<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 06 at 4:38PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Warren,
Glascock and north central Washington Counties through 515 PM EDT...
At 438 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Agricola, or 8 miles
southwest of Gibson, moving northeast at 50 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Gibson, Mitchell, Edge Hill, Edgehill, Hamburg State Park, Agricola,
Reese, Bastonville and Shoals.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 700 PM EDT for east central
Georgia.</instruction>
